Green politician must answer for embarrassing photo booth
The leader of the Canadian Green Party, Elizabeth May, in the election campaign - was the cup manipulated for this reason?
The Canadian Green Party leader is pictured holding a disposable cup, but now it's come out that the cup was manipulated.
Ottawa, Canada - It went unnoticed for quite a while - and finally caught on. The reusable coffee cup with metal straw was never held by Elizabeth May, the leader of the Canadian Greens. On the party's website, she was seen in a photo with the cup, talking to citizens. However, the photo had already been published and circulated to the media - and the cup was still a snot cup, as the Canadian National Post reported.
Green leader must answer for photo-crash
The National Post then accused May of manipulation and the party of producing fake news to make itself more credible on the issue of "environmental protection", and this in the midst of a campaign for the House of Commons election in which Trudeau is also increasingly struggling over a bribery scandal.
