On the return flight, Jaqueline tried again to upgrade to the long-haul flight, and this time the woman reportedly showed the same email, but with a different reference number. The staff at JFK Airport were skeptical, so they checked with the headquarters. In fact, the employee who allegedly sent the email denied that he had emailed Jaqueline, which was confirmed by the email system, which did not show the messages.
The airline staff at the airport cancelled Jaqueline's ticket and banned her from flying with Cathay Pacific for life, forcing her to buy a new ticket to Taiwan for $1,400.
